The future of abortion in New Zealand is uncertain. The International Day of the Elimination of Violence against Women is 25 November, and this is one of four new Feminist movements born out of the global Women’s March of 21 January 2017. One of these groups, "Matrescence", explained their goals thus;

Using the platform created by the Me Too movement we plan to remind everyone that for many women a positive experience during this one extremely vulnerable period grants the opportunity to view the world through a more benevolent lens. We would like to encourage new mothers to use the power of their newly capacitated minds and lending voices to mitigate women’s vulnerability upon returning to the workforce. Everwhere in the world pregnant women, new mothers and their families are victims of violence and discrimination in their communities, workplaces, homes, hospital and in society within all countries, Davidson said.[6]
